WiM x MUSA: Pauline Sperry Lecture with Dr. Kelli Talaska
We are hosting a joint lecture series between WiM and MUSA in honor of Dr. Pauline Sperry who was the first woman to become an associate mathematics professor at UC Berkeley. Dr. Sperry joined the mathematics department in 1917 as an instructor and was awarded the assistant professorship in 1923. She was later promoted to associate professor in 1931 and was given the title of Associate Professor Of Mathematics Emeritus in 1952. She was an incredible mathematician, an exceptional teacher, and a prominent activist.
To celebrate Dr. Sperry’s impact on the mathematical community, we are celebrating women in mathematics who exemplify these same qualities of inspiring mentorship and compassionate leadership.

Time: Dec 3, 2020 06:00 PM Pacific Time (US and Canada)
